---
source: clash/tests/cli_help_snapshots.rs
assertion_line: 18
expression: get_help(&cmd)
---
Command line agent safety harness

Usage: clash [OPTIONS] <COMMAND>

Commands:
  init        Initialize a new clash policy with a safe default configuration
  uninstall   Remove clash: undo bypass permissions, uninstall plugin, remove config and binary
  status      Show policy status: layers, rules with shadowing, and potential issues
  policy      View and manage policy rules
  commands    Print the full command and subcommand hierarchy
  shell       Run a bash-compatible shell with per-command sandbox enforcement
  sandbox     Apply sandbox restrictions and exec commands
  doctor      Diagnose common setup issues and report fix instructions
  debug       Debug policy enforcement: view logs, replay commands, inspect sandbox
  trace       View and export session traces
  session     List, inspect, and locate session directories
  fmt         Format Starlark policy files using ruff
  explain     Explain which policy rule would match a given tool invocation
  update      Update clash to the latest release (or a specific version)
  statusline  Display clash status in the Claude Code status line
  help        Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)

Options:
  -v, --verbose  
  -h, --help     Print help
  -V, --version  Print version
